               <head>Bond; Needham Street; 1338</head>
               <msContents><textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_111667">Needham Street (Needham-Street)</placeName>. 
                        <origDate when="1338">1338</origDate>. 
                        Bond from <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Aumener</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName>
                        </persName> to <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Nichole</surname>
                        </persName> of the same, undertaking for himself and <persName nymRef="Aumener">his wife <forename>Joan</forename></persName>, to pay to Thomas 40 shillings in the event of his being disppossessed, by writ at the plea of the said Joan, of 2.5 acres of land, wherewith John has enfeoffed him.
                        Dated, at <placeName role="date" key="place_111667">Needham Street (Nedham)</placeName> on Friday [18 Sept.] after the feast of the Exaltation of the Holy Cross, 12 Ed. III [1338]
                     </p>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
